1
00:00:00,500 --> 00:00:02,940
Starting today,
I'm joining the sales department.

2
00:00:02,940 --> 00:00:04,830
I'm Eisei Ureshino.

3
00:00:04,830 --> 00:00:08,640
Don't you feel like this is fate?

4
00:00:08,640 --> 00:00:13,625
Reunion sex with the man
I cheated with 10 years ago.

5
00:00:13,625 --> 00:00:18,830
Wait, so it's been two whole days
since we reunited?

6
00:00:18,830 --> 00:00:22,570
Seriously, what the heck is this?

7
00:00:22,570 --> 00:00:23,740
Hey.

8
00:00:23,740 --> 00:00:26,565
Why do you think I call you "Miporin"?

9
00:00:26,565 --> 00:00:28,890
Right now,

10
00:00:28,890 --> 00:00:33,990
we're closer than we've ever been.

11
00:00:33,990 --> 00:00:35,930
We're not dating.

12
00:00:35,930 --> 00:00:38,610
I don't want to just be
a convenient guy to have around.

13
00:00:38,610 --> 00:00:41,440
Looks like she got rejected by Ureshino-san.

14
00:00:41,440 --> 00:00:43,820
Who cares about the rumors?

15
00:00:43,820 --> 00:00:45,525
It's a bother.

16
00:00:45,525 --> 00:00:47,295
Fine.

17
00:00:52,270 --> 00:00:56,920
How about we go for it?

18
00:00:59,640 --> 00:01:01,140
Huh?

19
00:01:05,220 --> 00:01:10,280
What if we... actually started dating?

20
00:01:21,810 --> 00:01:24,860
You're saying that now?

21
00:01:24,860 --> 00:01:26,810
Think it over.

22
00:01:36,530 --> 00:01:40,650
I think I like you.

23
00:01:45,760 --> 00:01:48,240
You're so cute, Miporin.

24
00:01:51,530 --> 00:01:57,220
That's the one thing
I kept trying to block out...

25
00:02:00,360 --> 00:02:02,290
What are you saying now

26
00:02:03,470 --> 00:02:05,690
after all this time?

27
00:02:09,480 --> 00:02:13,220
♫ It's hard to resist the thing
that I've missed for so long ♫

28
00:02:13,220 --> 00:02:15,080
♫ So long ♫

29
00:02:15,080 --> 00:02:18,860
♫ Can't remember what it's like,
Just remember I need it ♫

30
00:02:18,860 --> 00:02:21,300
♫ I need it ♫

31
00:02:21,300 --> 00:02:25,510
♫ You're not what I thought you were ♫

32
00:02:25,510 --> 00:02:27,470
♫ You were ♫

33
00:02:27,470 --> 00:02:30,810
♫ To think I can't find a cure ♫

34
00:02:30,810 --> 00:02:33,450
♫ Find a cure ♫

35
00:02:33,450 --> 00:02:39,530
♫ Ooh, you're not what I thought ♫

36
00:02:42,700 --> 00:02:50,000
[If Only You Weren't the One]

37
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:56,130
[Episode 7]

38
00:02:59,870 --> 00:03:03,480
What if we actually started dating?

39
00:03:09,690 --> 00:03:13,747
[Kusaka-kun: Onuma-san,
do you have plans on the 24th?]

40
00:03:16,050 --> 00:03:18,190
Christmas Eve, huh?

41
00:03:29,116 --> 00:03:34,817
[Are you free on the night of the 24th?]

42
00:03:43,490 --> 00:03:48,862
[I already have plans that day! lol]

43
00:03:52,100 --> 00:03:57,430
Ugh, I really hate you.

44
00:04:05,910 --> 00:04:09,040
It's not fair.

45
00:04:28,620 --> 00:04:30,200
[Kusaka-kun]

46
00:04:30,200 --> 00:04:32,320
[Thank you, I'm waiting to hear from you.]

47
00:04:32,320 --> 00:04:33,900
[I appreciate it.]

48
00:04:33,900 --> 00:04:35,990
[Onuma-san, do you have plans on the 24th?]

49
00:04:35,990 --> 00:04:37,998
[I'm free.]

50
00:04:41,710 --> 00:04:45,680
[Merry Christmas]

51
00:04:48,790 --> 00:04:52,140
Is it okay that we came here again?

52
00:04:52,140 --> 00:04:54,910
Yeah. This place is nice.

53
00:04:54,910 --> 00:04:56,865
The food is good too,

54
00:04:56,865 --> 00:05:00,425
so I actually wanted to come back.

55
00:05:01,090 --> 00:05:04,820
I'm glad you feel that way.

56
00:05:06,310 --> 00:05:12,570
Actually, I didn't think you'd agree
to meet me on Christmas Eve.

57
00:05:15,980 --> 00:05:19,000
So, um...

58
00:05:19,830 --> 00:05:23,880
I'm thinking of asking for the wine list.

59
00:05:24,835 --> 00:05:26,150
Okay.

60
00:05:26,150 --> 00:05:28,070
But before that,

61
00:05:29,050 --> 00:05:31,630
I want to tell you something.

62
00:05:39,720 --> 00:05:41,580
Onuma-san...

63
00:05:46,060 --> 00:05:49,200
I like you. Please go out with me.

64
00:05:52,180 --> 00:05:54,120
Huh?

65
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:57,890
I wanted to say it properly,
while I'm still sober.

66
00:05:59,260 --> 00:06:01,060
Oh...

67
00:06:01,060 --> 00:06:02,950
Thank you.

68
00:06:03,670 --> 00:06:07,040
Sorry, it's not very romantic.

69
00:06:07,800 --> 00:06:10,990
But I want it to be proper.

70
00:06:10,990 --> 00:06:13,270
Our relationship, I mean.

71
00:06:19,455 --> 00:06:23,940
Oh, you can feel free to drink.

72
00:06:23,940 --> 00:06:27,450
It's not like I need an answer right now.

73
00:06:31,095 --> 00:06:32,530
Excuse me.

74
00:06:32,530 --> 00:06:34,470
Could we have the wine list?

75
00:06:34,470 --> 00:06:36,390
Certainly.

76
00:06:41,247 --> 00:06:43,367
Thank you.

77
00:06:49,520 --> 00:06:54,040
But actually, I don't know much about wine.

78
00:06:56,460 --> 00:06:58,830
I wonder what's good.

79
00:06:59,600 --> 00:07:03,040
Onuma-san, do you drink wine or other alcohol?

80
00:07:03,720 --> 00:07:07,200
Maybe a full-bodied one is too heavy.

81
00:07:07,200 --> 00:07:09,620
They have champagne too.

82
00:07:12,580 --> 00:07:14,360
Thank you.

83
00:07:15,630 --> 00:07:18,890
Oh, I'm sorry.

84
00:07:18,890 --> 00:07:21,270
I made you uncomfortable.

85
00:07:22,709 --> 00:07:27,720
I'm the one who made you uncomfortable.

86
00:07:27,720 --> 00:07:30,180
That's not true.

87
00:07:32,900 --> 00:07:39,120
Even knowing how you feel,
I'm still acting half-heartedly.

88
00:07:44,920 --> 00:07:50,400
I was happy to hear from you the other day.

89
00:07:52,660 --> 00:07:55,490
It made me think...

90
00:07:55,490 --> 00:08:00,340
you were becoming
a tiny bit more serious about me.

91
00:08:01,585 --> 00:08:03,430
A tiny bit?

92
00:08:03,430 --> 00:08:05,380
It's a joke.

93
00:08:08,200 --> 00:08:09,740
But...

94
00:08:12,192 --> 00:08:16,829
that suddenly made me scared.

95
00:08:20,420 --> 00:08:23,400
So, I wanted to confess before I got rejected.

96
00:08:30,290 --> 00:08:33,010
I'm pretty selfish too, huh?

97
00:08:41,140 --> 00:08:43,250
Kusaka-kun...

98
00:08:52,030 --> 00:08:56,000
You don't have to answer right away.

99
00:08:59,520 --> 00:09:01,500
I'm sorry.

100
00:09:04,400 --> 00:09:09,250
If things stay like this...

101
00:09:09,250 --> 00:09:13,756
I feel like I'll take advantage of you.

102
00:09:21,160 --> 00:09:22,990
I'm sorry.

103
00:09:33,460 --> 00:09:36,600
But you didn't have to tell me right away...

104
00:10:54,988 --> 00:10:57,130
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

105
00:10:57,130 --> 00:10:58,380
No, that's not it.

106
00:10:58,380 --> 00:10:59,965
You're totally lying.

107
00:10:59,965 --> 00:11:02,505
I'm jealous. You're so sly.

108
00:11:02,505 --> 00:11:05,055
Maybe just a little.

109
00:11:18,805 --> 00:11:20,747
Excuse me.

110
00:11:20,747 --> 00:11:26,225
Can you process my expenses
for entertaining Seiyo Airways yesterday?

111
00:11:26,225 --> 00:11:28,145
Yesterday?

112
00:11:29,120 --> 00:11:33,120
I was working, even on Christmas Eve.

113
00:11:33,120 --> 00:11:35,520
It's pretty sad, isn't it?

114
00:11:45,810 --> 00:11:49,020
Yes. All right.

115
00:11:49,020 --> 00:11:52,935
I'll check on that for you.

116
00:11:52,935 --> 00:11:53,920
- Okay.
- See you.

117
00:11:53,920 --> 00:11:57,065
- See you.
- One moment.

118
00:11:57,065 --> 00:11:58,385
Onuma-san?

119
00:11:58,385 --> 00:12:01,379
- Can I have a moment?
- Okay.

120
00:12:01,379 --> 00:12:03,180
It's Maihoku Shuttle.

121
00:12:03,180 --> 00:12:06,988
Did you pay the invoice
we received at the end of last month?

122
00:12:06,988 --> 00:12:09,980
- Huh?
- They're angry that it's not paid yet.

123
00:12:09,980 --> 00:12:11,365
No way... I'm sorry.

124
00:12:11,365 --> 00:12:14,050
- Can you check?
- Okay.

125
00:12:16,200 --> 00:12:18,270
Should I take over?

126
00:12:19,295 --> 00:12:21,410
It's Daidoji-san, right?

127
00:12:21,410 --> 00:12:22,370
Yes.

128
00:12:22,370 --> 00:12:24,870
They just emailed me about something else.

129
00:12:24,870 --> 00:12:29,150
I'm on good terms with them,
so let me explain and apologize.

130
00:12:29,150 --> 00:12:34,094
Oh, really? Would you mind then?

131
00:12:36,610 --> 00:12:40,850
Hello, this is Ureshino.

132
00:12:40,850 --> 00:12:45,680
We deeply apologize for our mistake this time.

133
00:12:45,680 --> 00:12:47,180
Yes.

134
00:12:47,925 --> 00:12:49,770
I am really sorry.

135
00:12:49,770 --> 00:12:52,475
- Bye.
- Not at all.

136
00:12:52,475 --> 00:12:54,840
Thank you.

137
00:12:54,840 --> 00:12:58,505
Okay, thank you for understanding.

138
00:12:58,505 --> 00:13:01,525
Yes, thank you.

139
00:13:02,490 --> 00:13:05,380
All right. Sorry to trouble you.

140
00:13:44,091 --> 00:13:46,600
I'm really sorry about earlier.

141
00:13:46,600 --> 00:13:48,075
Thank you.

142
00:13:48,075 --> 00:13:52,780
Don't worry about it.
Everyone makes mistakes.

143
00:13:52,780 --> 00:13:56,560
Even Daidoji-san said
he's sorry for snapping earlier.

144
00:13:56,560 --> 00:13:58,675
Don't let it get to you.

145
00:13:58,675 --> 00:14:00,555
Thanks.

146
00:14:01,300 --> 00:14:05,170
But knowing you,
you're still going to worry about it.

147
00:14:05,930 --> 00:14:08,780
I like that about you.

148
00:14:11,825 --> 00:14:14,970
Oh, by the way, sorry about yesterday.

149
00:14:14,970 --> 00:14:17,700
- Huh?
- Your invitation for Christmas Eve.

150
00:14:17,700 --> 00:14:19,755
Oh, that's fine.

151
00:14:19,755 --> 00:14:22,085
Good work yesterday.

152
00:14:23,150 --> 00:14:24,860
Thanks.

153
00:14:26,660 --> 00:14:31,070
Oh, it's still Christmas today, right?

154
00:14:31,070 --> 00:14:33,380
I guess so.

155
00:14:33,380 --> 00:14:35,880
Our first Christmas together.

156
00:14:35,880 --> 00:14:37,470
Yeah.

157
00:14:37,470 --> 00:14:40,840
Back then, we couldn't meet up.

158
00:14:40,840 --> 00:14:42,230
You remember that?

159
00:14:42,230 --> 00:14:45,350
Of course. I wanted to see you.

160
00:14:45,350 --> 00:14:50,330
You can say stuff like that so easily.

161
00:14:50,330 --> 00:14:51,825
Huh?

162
00:14:51,825 --> 00:14:54,745
Without having any idea how I feel.

163
00:14:55,537 --> 00:14:59,150
The feeling's mutual, you know.

164
00:14:59,150 --> 00:15:00,330
Huh?

165
00:15:00,330 --> 00:15:03,225
- Don't "huh" me.
- How could I not?

166
00:15:03,225 --> 00:15:05,425
You can't be serious.

167
00:15:12,440 --> 00:15:13,970
All right then.

168
00:15:17,270 --> 00:15:19,150
What's wrong?

169
00:15:21,150 --> 00:15:23,150
Are you going home?

170
00:15:24,360 --> 00:15:26,320
Yes, for today.

171
00:15:28,020 --> 00:15:29,760
I see.

172
00:15:31,400 --> 00:15:34,075
I think it's for the best.

173
00:15:34,075 --> 00:15:36,070
Just my gut feeling.

174
00:15:36,070 --> 00:15:38,030
That makes no sense.

175
00:15:38,680 --> 00:15:40,730
Well, see you later.

176
00:15:42,980 --> 00:15:44,670
Hey!

177
00:15:50,360 --> 00:15:52,630
Thanks for today.

178
00:15:55,370 --> 00:15:57,320
You owe me one!

179
00:16:15,260 --> 00:16:20,280
Jeez, I hate this so much.

180
00:16:43,865 --> 00:16:45,204
Mihono-san.

181
00:16:45,204 --> 00:16:46,860
- Yuri-chan.
- Good work.

182
00:16:46,860 --> 00:16:48,110
Good work.

183
00:16:48,110 --> 00:16:50,925
There's tons of good food.
Let's eat together.

184
00:16:50,925 --> 00:16:53,990
Oh, thank you. Let's go over there.

185
00:16:53,990 --> 00:16:58,000
- Get me some fried shrimp.
- Leave it to me.

186
00:16:58,000 --> 00:17:00,340
- You're eating all of them?
- I can't stop.

187
00:17:00,340 --> 00:17:02,110
- I can't stop eating fried shrimps.
- They’re so easy

188
00:17:02,110 --> 00:17:04,480
- to eat, right?
- Two for you.

189
00:17:04,480 --> 00:17:06,700
- Thank you. Oh, even more.
- It's a free extra.

190
00:17:06,700 --> 00:17:08,180
Thank you.

191
00:17:08,180 --> 00:17:11,000
I'll eat it.

192
00:17:14,060 --> 00:17:15,680
Um...

193
00:17:17,137 --> 00:17:22,440
I'm sorry about the other day
for taking it out on you.

194
00:17:22,440 --> 00:17:24,040
It's fine.

195
00:17:26,613 --> 00:17:31,580
That was the first time
I asked someone out.

196
00:17:31,580 --> 00:17:33,900
It was really scary.

197
00:17:34,690 --> 00:17:37,740
And, well...

198
00:17:39,763 --> 00:17:43,950
Actually, I was pretty hurt.

199
00:17:43,950 --> 00:17:45,740
I see.

200
00:17:50,830 --> 00:17:52,430
But...

201
00:17:54,060 --> 00:17:56,410
it was a good experience.

202
00:17:59,112 --> 00:18:04,170
When I got rejected, I seriously thought
about quitting the company.

203
00:18:04,170 --> 00:18:08,050
But when I actually thought about quitting,

204
00:18:08,050 --> 00:18:11,320
I realized that I like this job,

205
00:18:11,320 --> 00:18:13,470
I like this company,

206
00:18:13,470 --> 00:18:15,815
and that I didn't want to quit.

207
00:18:15,815 --> 00:18:19,015
Eventually, that was all I could think about.

208
00:18:20,260 --> 00:18:26,170
It made me realize there's more
to my life than just Ureshino-san.

209
00:18:27,590 --> 00:18:31,000
There are so many other things I like.

210
00:18:33,420 --> 00:18:39,410
Besides, I really didn't want to lose
being able to talk to you like this.

211
00:18:40,520 --> 00:18:42,700
So...

212
00:18:42,700 --> 00:18:44,530
I'm sorry.

213
00:18:45,910 --> 00:18:47,640
It's fine.

214
00:18:49,030 --> 00:18:51,270
Thank you, Yuri-chan.

215
00:18:52,599 --> 00:18:55,510
- Let's eat.
- Yes, let's do that.

216
00:18:55,510 --> 00:18:59,225
- What's this?
- It's shrimp. I love shrimp.

217
00:18:59,225 --> 00:19:01,690
- Doesn't this have shrimp too?
- Oh, really?

218
00:19:01,690 --> 00:19:04,350
Hello! Excuse me
for interrupting your conversation!

219
00:19:04,350 --> 00:19:05,940
All right.

220
00:19:05,940 --> 00:19:13,250
I'd like to honor two representatives
from the project team,

221
00:19:13,250 --> 00:19:15,780
the pride of our Sales Department,

222
00:19:15,780 --> 00:19:18,990
who achieved the highest sales this year!

223
00:19:18,990 --> 00:19:21,750
Great!

224
00:19:21,750 --> 00:19:24,255
Kusaka-kun!

225
00:19:24,255 --> 00:19:27,150
And... Ureshino-kun!

226
00:19:27,150 --> 00:19:29,236
Whoa!

227
00:19:29,236 --> 00:19:33,445
- Congratulations!
- Congratulations!

228
00:19:33,445 --> 00:19:36,900
A certificate of commendation!

229
00:19:36,900 --> 00:19:40,774
You've made great contributions
to the company's growth.

230
00:19:40,774 --> 00:19:46,169
Therefore, we highly praise
your achievements with this award.

231
00:19:46,169 --> 00:19:48,375
From Worldrise Travel Co., Ltd.

232
00:19:48,375 --> 00:19:52,282
Representative Director, Kazunari Iwamoto.

233
00:19:52,282 --> 00:19:54,800
- Congratulations!
- Well done!

234
00:20:13,185 --> 00:20:15,280
The year's almost over, huh?

235
00:20:15,280 --> 00:20:17,120
Yeah.

236
00:20:17,120 --> 00:20:21,440
Can you stand not meeting Ureshino-san
until next year?

237
00:20:21,440 --> 00:20:22,815
Huh?

238
00:20:22,815 --> 00:20:26,690
Everyone knows, Miporin.

239
00:20:26,690 --> 00:20:27,950
Hey!

240
00:20:27,950 --> 00:20:30,350
Happy New Year.

241
00:20:35,320 --> 00:20:36,790
Yes!

242
00:20:36,790 --> 00:20:37,910
Come on.

243
00:20:37,910 --> 00:20:40,880
- Who's up for a second round?
- Me!

244
00:20:40,880 --> 00:20:43,000
- Who wants karaoke?
- Me!

245
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:46,800
- Mihono-san, are you coming?
- Wow, I'm not sure.

246
00:20:46,800 --> 00:20:49,070
Tomorrow's a holiday, so maybe just a bit.

247
00:20:49,070 --> 00:20:50,640
I'm jealous.

248
00:20:50,640 --> 00:20:53,320
I'm visiting my parents
on the last train tonight.

249
00:20:53,320 --> 00:20:54,820
Oh, really?

250
00:20:54,820 --> 00:20:57,195
Take it easy, and have a Happy New Year.

251
00:20:57,195 --> 00:21:00,165
Thank you. You too, Mihono-san.

252
00:21:05,432 --> 00:21:08,420
Oh... I forgot something.

253
00:21:08,420 --> 00:21:10,920
The hot spring invitation tickets.

254
00:21:10,920 --> 00:21:12,585
I was going to send them to my parents.

255
00:21:12,585 --> 00:21:17,311
Oh, nice! I'm sure they'll love it.

256
00:21:17,311 --> 00:21:19,295
I'll go get them. See you next year.

257
00:21:19,295 --> 00:21:21,085
See you next year!

258
00:21:37,970 --> 00:21:39,410
Hey.

259
00:21:40,325 --> 00:21:42,180
Why are you here?

260
00:21:42,180 --> 00:21:45,160
I should be asking you that.

261
00:21:45,160 --> 00:21:47,730
Don't just slip away by yourself.

262
00:21:53,785 --> 00:21:55,950
Hey...

263
00:21:55,950 --> 00:21:58,975
- Are you drunk?
- No.

264
00:22:03,650 --> 00:22:05,090
Huh?

265
00:22:26,230 --> 00:22:28,010
I like you.

266
00:22:40,770 --> 00:22:42,400
Me too.

267
00:22:58,290 --> 00:23:04,970
♫ We walked through the city at daybreak,
soaked by the rain ♫

268
00:23:04,970 --> 00:23:09,780
♫ You and me in the rain ♫

269
00:23:10,880 --> 00:23:17,280
♫ Rather than trusting others, I want to be... ♫

270
00:23:17,280 --> 00:23:19,050
The second round.

271
00:23:20,580 --> 00:23:23,130
Let's skip out on it.

272
